From a31b8f11d3b8140e9831d4f281a9a839bdf2aa21 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Guillaume Ausset <guillaume@ausset.me>
Date: Fri, 13 Mar 2026 17:45:00 +0100
Subject: [PATCH] ports/rp2: reset HCI scheduler state across soft reset

After fixing the rp2 BTstack run loop to execute deferred callbacks, H10
PSFTP pairing became reliable immediately after a hard reset, but still
regressed across MicroPython soft resets.

The rp2 HCI scheduling glue keeps two pieces of state outside the
MicroPython VM heap:
- the one-shot soft timer used to reschedule polls
- the static scheduler node used for immediate poll requests

If a soft reset happens while Bluetooth work is pending, that state can
leak across interpreter lifetimes. On the next run the rp2 BTstack path
can then miss immediate polls or keep stale timer state, which correlates
with pairing stalling again after Just Works confirmation.

Reset that scheduling state explicitly by:
- clearing the static scheduler node on HCI init
- removing the outstanding HCI soft timer on HCI deinit
- calling the new HCI deinit hook from the BTstack rp2 port shutdown path

This keeps the rp2 HCI scheduler state aligned with the surrounding
MicroPython soft-reset lifecycle.

---
 ports/rp2/mpbthciport.c | 6 ++++++
 ports/rp2/mpbthciport.h | 3 ++-
 ports/rp2/mpbtstackport.c | 1 +
 3 files changed, 9 insertions(+), 1 deletion(-)

diff --git a/ports/rp2/mpbthciport.c b/ports/rp2/mpbthciport.c
index 0112304..1243b87 100644
--- a/ports/rp2/mpbthciport.c
+++ b/ports/rp2/mpbthciport.c
@@ -57,6 +57,12 @@ void mp_bluetooth_hci_init(void) {
         0,
         mp_bluetooth_hci_soft_timer_callback
         );
+    mp_bluetooth_hci_sched_node.callback = NULL;
+    mp_bluetooth_hci_sched_node.next = NULL;
+}
+
+void mp_bluetooth_hci_deinit(void) {
+    soft_timer_remove(&mp_bluetooth_hci_soft_timer);
 }
 
 void mp_bluetooth_hci_poll_in_ms(uint32_t ms) {
diff --git a/ports/rp2/mpbthciport.h b/ports/rp2/mpbthciport.h
index fdf46c5..e1c2222 100644
--- a/ports/rp2/mpbthciport.h
+++ b/ports/rp2/mpbthciport.h
@@ -26,8 +26,9 @@
 #ifndef MICROPY_INCLUDED_RP2_MPBTHCIPORT_H
 #define MICROPY_INCLUDED_RP2_MPBTHCIPORT_H
 
-// Initialise the HCI subsystem (should be called once, early on).
+// Initialise/deinitialise the HCI scheduling subsystem.
 void mp_bluetooth_hci_init(void);
+void mp_bluetooth_hci_deinit(void);
 
 // Poll the HCI now, or after a certain timeout.
 void mp_bluetooth_hci_poll_now(void);
diff --git a/ports/rp2/mpbtstackport.c b/ports/rp2/mpbtstackport.c
index d4f03c3..a4c57c1 100644
--- a/ports/rp2/mpbtstackport.c
+++ b/ports/rp2/mpbtstackport.c
@@ -150,6 +150,7 @@ void mp_bluetooth_btstack_port_init(void) {
 }
 
 void mp_bluetooth_btstack_port_deinit(void) {
+    mp_bluetooth_hci_deinit();
     hci_power_control(HCI_POWER_OFF);
     // We really need hci to be closed or else we might get a BT interrupt going off and
     // this will cause a crash when calling btstack_run_loop_poll_data_sources_from_irq after the btstack run loop has been deleted
-- 
